article.headline: Hampton 74, Florida A&M 72, OT
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Theo Smalling made a layup with 3:41 left in overtime to put Hampton ahead for good in a 74-72 victory over Florida A&M on Monday night. The Rattlers (13-11, 7-4 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) were up by 2 points with 1:03 to play, but Michael Freeman made a layup with 48 seconds remaining to tie it 64-64. Freeman led the Pirates (9-12, 6-5) with 23 points and six rebounds, and Rashad West added 22 points. Rome Sanders had 18 points and seven rebounds for the Rattlers, and Ernest Maul added 15 points. Florida A&M outshot Hampton 48.2 percent to 35.6 percent. The Pirates outrebounded the Rattlers 44-42.
